'''《圣哉三一歌》'''，或依歌词首句称作'''《圣哉，圣哉，圣哉》'''（{{lang-en|'''"Holy, Holy, Holy"'''}}）是一首[[基督教|基督教]][[赞美诗|赞美诗]]。歌词取材于{{cuv|以赛亚书|6|1|5}}，是[[雷金纳德·希伯|雷金纳德·希伯]]<ref name="brown2008" /><ref name="sankey2008" /><ref name="osbeck1982" />为[[圣三一主日|圣三一主日]]而作<ref name="osbeck1982" />，着重阐述基督教“[[三位一体|三位一体]]”[[基督教中的神|神论]]的要义。[[约翰·巴克斯·戴克斯|约翰·巴克斯·戴克斯]]（John Bacchus Dykes）于1861年依词作曲<ref name="brown2008">{{cite book |first = Theron |last = Brown |coauthors = [[Hezekiah_Butterworth|Hezekiah Butterworth]] |chapter = Holy, Holy, Holy! Lord God Almighty! |chapterurl = http://books.google.com/books?id=yw80zS-vcvEC&pg=PA66 |title = The Story of the Hymns and Tunes |publisher = BiblioBazaar |location =  |year = 2008 |origyear = 1906 |page = 66 |isbn = 0-554-25576-6 |access-date = 2012-02-05 |archive-date = 2019-04-22 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190422085311/https://books.google.com/books?id=yw80zS-vcvEC&pg=PA66 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="sankey2008">{{cite book |first=Ira David |last=Sankey |authorlink=Ira D. Sankey |chapter=Holy, Holy, Holy, Lord God Almighty |chapterurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=RM2EAz7VNP0C&pg=PA364 |title=My Life and the Story of the Gospel Hymns and of Sacred Songs and Solos |publisher=BiblioBazaar |location= |year=2008 |origyear=1907 |pages=364–365 |isbn=0-559-33724-8 |access-date=2012-02-05 |archive-date=2019-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422085313/https://books.google.com/books?id=RM2EAz7VNP0C&pg=PA364 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="osbeck1982">{{cite book |first = Kenneth W. |last = Osbeck |chapter = Holy, Holy, Holy |chapterurl = http://books.google.com/books?id=kN-FilvMftwC&pg=RA1-PA31-IA1 |title = 101 hymn stories |publisher = Kregel Publications |location = [[Grand_Rapids,_Michigan|Grand Rapids, Michigan]] |year = 1982 |pages = 94–95 |isbn = 0-8254-3416-5 |oclc = 7875830 |access-date = 2012-02-05 |archive-date = 2019-04-22 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190422085308/https://books.google.com/books?id=kN-FilvMftwC&pg=RA1-PA31-IA1 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。
